Package de.fraunhofer.iais.eis

Class LogicalConstraintImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.fraunhofer.iais.eis.LogicalConstraintImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AbstractConstraint, LogicalConstraint, ModelClass
    public class LogicalConstraintImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements LogicalConstraint
    Default implementation of package de.fraunhofer.iais.eis.LogicalConstraint The class of Logical Constraints that restrict a Rule. A Logical Constraints is a collection of Constraints, related with each other through the ids:operand property.

        public java.util.List<Constraint> getAnd()
        Description copied from interface: LogicalConstraint
        The 'and' operand connects a rdf:List of Constraints with the Boolean operator 'AND'. All Constraints of an 'and' relation must be satisfied at the same time. Only one of ids:and, ids:or, or ids:xone can be used for a specific ids:LogicalConstraint! More information under https://w3id.org/idsa/core/and
